{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Ren et al. [119] focused on the secure cell-free ISAC system design, where the transmit beamforming vectors at multiple collaborative ISAC-BSs were jointly optimized to maximize the target detection probability.",
    "Lyu et al. [121] deployed an IRS to assist both communication and sensing, and the CRB of angle estimation was minimized via the joint hybrid beamforming and phase-shift optimization.",
    "Zhao et al. [122] investigated the robust beamforming optimization problem for ISAC systems, where the maximum CRB of multi-target direction of arrival estimation was minimized subject to the SINR constraint at each user.",
    "Transceiver designFor the ISAC performance enhancement, the receive-side precessing is as important as the waveform design, becoming the focus of many researchers.",
    "Tsinos et al. [180] first investigated the joint transmitted waveform and receive filter design for ISAC networks, and proposed an effective algorithm to handle this non-convex optimization problem."
  ],
